01:17:25.000 --> 01:17:29.000
Thus, the structure of regulations will allow us to understand

01:17:29.000 --> 01:17:33.000
the role of a person in an organization or department,

01:17:33.000 --> 01:17:37.000
and the process one will help us understand the role of this action,

01:17:37.000 --> 01:17:41.000
the overall process of the organization.

01:17:41.000 --> 01:17:45.000
Let's say, we have a position on the process of the highest level.

01:17:45.000 --> 01:17:49.000
Here are described the inputs and outputs of the process,

01:17:49.000 --> 01:17:53.000
the responsible ones,

01:17:53.000 --> 01:17:57.000
and from which procedures this process consists,

01:17:57.000 --> 01:18:01.000
if we speak roughly.

01:18:01.000 --> 01:18:05.000
Then we talk about each procedure that is included in this business process.

01:18:05.000 --> 01:18:09.000
And only then we talk about specific small operations.

01:18:09.000 --> 01:18:13.000
If we talk about the mistakes that are most often made by those who start the business processes regulation.

01:18:23.000 --> 01:18:27.000
Number one.

01:18:27.000 --> 01:18:31.000
